# Git: always commit and push

After finishing meaningful work:

1. Commit local changes (status → diff → log → stage → commit).
2. Push the current branch to `origin`.

Do this by default without waiting for a separate ask.

Never force-push main/master unless explicitly requested. Never skip hooks or update git config. Never commit secrets.
